[The city of Xi'an seems well on the way to achieving eradication of measles virus infection among the non-migrant population at least.

Xi'an is the capital of Shaanxi province and a sub-provincial city in the People's Republic of China. It is one of the oldest cities in China, with more than 3000 years of history. The city was known as Chang'an before the Ming Dynasty. Xi'an is one of the Four Great Ancient Capitals of China, having held the position under several of the most important dynasties in Chinese history.

Shaanxi province can be located in the interactive ProMED/HealthMap at: http://healthmap.org/r/3H_0. - Mod.CP]

